node.text:
Since the founding of the ERAU Spacesuit Utilization of Innovative Technology Laboratory (S.U.I.T. Lab) in 2017, students have completed many exciting projects, including ones that are highlighted in this video made by @spacesuitup!
The lab is a testbed for spacesuit design research where students get to work with industry partners to develop innovative solutions. Visit erau.edu/spacesuit for more information about the team! 🚀👨‍🚀🛰 #spacesuitup

Fall semester check-in and move-in begins in just one week! 🦅 Are you excited?! 🎉

Here's what to expect during your drive-in and check-in experience. Learn more at daytonabeach.erau.edu/campus-life/orientation (linked in our Stories!) #GoERAU #ERAUOrientation

node.text:
New telescopes 🔭 coming to the observation deck on the roof of the College of Arts and Sciences! 💫

Funded by a research project for satellite tracking, the new equipment will be used to accommodate the booming enrollments in the Astronomy and Astrophysics bachelor’s program. 🦅

The new refractor telescopes are six inches in diameter and, with the associated cameras, can detect light that is several thousand times fainter than the naked eye. 🌃

#GoERAU #telescopes #space #astronomy #astrophysics #STEM

node.text:
Beep beep — food delivery robot coming through! 🤖

Meet the fleet of @starshiprobots that will be roaming campus to make meal time easier for Eagles. 🦅

On-demand, zero-emission deliveries will now be part of the dining options offered by @erau_eats, providing a greener way for Eagles to score quick meals. Use the Starship Food Delivery app (iOS and Android) to order food and drinks from local retailers to be delivered anywhere on campus, within minutes. 🌯🍔🥗☕️🌮🍕🍟

#GoERAU #robots #autonomous #fooddeliveryrobot #starshiptechnologies #starshiprobots #campuslife #collegecampus

node.text:
In celebration of #NationalWomensDay, we're recognizing triple alumna Jayde King, who is paving the way for women of color in the Human Factors discipline.

From starting her journey as an Eagle at her South Florida high school to completing her doctorate in August 2020, King is the first Gaetz Aerospace Institute graduate to earn a Ph.D. from Embry-Riddle. 🦅 #GoERAU #HumanFactors
